      • getMessagePositionEnumValue

        public Enum<?> getMessagePositionEnumValue()
        If the Minecraft version uses enum to assign message type into the packet, returns the Enum value to be used for this message type.

        Else, returns null.

        Returns:
        The enum value to use, if the system uses them; null, else.
        See Also:
        The method returning the byte to use if the server uses bytes.
